RBAC: ROLE BASED ACCESS CONTROL
With RBAC we can give set of limited permissions to users.
HOW TO CREATE USER
	1. Dashboard -> manage Jenkins -> users -> Create user
Create two users.
THEN DOWNLOAD Role-based Authorization strategy plugins
	2. Manage Jenkins -> Plugins -> Available plugins -> select Role-based Authorization plugin -> Install
	3. Configure:
Dashboard -> Manage Jenkins -> Security -> Security -> Authorization -> Role-based strategy -> save.
	4. Manage and assign Roles:
Dashboard -> manage and assign roles -> Manage role
		○ role 1: fresher -> Read
		○ role 2: Exp -> Administer
Add -> save
	5. click on Assign Roles
Add user
Type username -> OK -> select role
	6. How to add additional permission for a user
Dashboard -> manage Jenkins -> manage & assign roles -> Manage roles -> Select Build — To be able build jobs -> Select Create — To be able Create jobs -> Select configure — To be able to configure jobs
